Publish What You Pay is a global network of civil society organizations working to increase transparency and accountability in the extractive and government sectors.

Global Witness investigates and campaigns to change the system by exposing the natural resource-related economic networks behind corruption, conflict and environmental destruction. They find the facts, they uncover the story and they change the system.
ePaństwo Foundation develops technology tools that make information about the Polish government and local authorities more transparent.
Code.org® is a nonprofit dedicated to expanding access to computer science, and increasing participation by women and underrepresented students of color.
DoSomething.org harnesses the creative, active, wired energy of teens and unleashes it on causes they care about.

Anudip Foundation creates new-economy livelihood opportunities for impoverished youth, women, and minorities in rural and semi-urban areas of India by providing IT-based job skills training, job placement, and entrepreneur development services.
BRAC empowers the world’s poor through a comprehensive set of development initiatives.
Ark is an education charity that exists to make sure that all children, regardless of their background, have access to a great education and real choices in life.
Center for Global Development is a global think tank that leverages independent research and analysis to convert ideas into policies and programs.
BudgIT is a Lagos-based nonprofit that promotes civic participation and fiscal transparency in Nigeria.
